args: All right, let's get started! *whinny*\nAre you two ready?
What's wrong? You're not shy, are you?
Don't worry. I'll be right here with you,\nevery step of the way. I won't let\nanything bad happen.
Heh, okay. Let me show you how it's done.
Merry Dragonyule! We come bearing gifts\nfrom Saint Starfall!
All right, everyone, line up and wait\nyour turn.
Awww, they're adorable! I've never seen\na dragon Saint Starfall before.
Well I'll be darned. Dragons delivering\npresents, just like in Ilia's day!\nThank you kindly.
Well now. That went quite well,\nwouldn't you say?
Are you dressed as a reindeer, young man?
Ha ha, marvelous! And how lucky to be\ntowing such sweet little Saint Starfalls.
We're very fortunate to be visited by such\nkind and devoted dragons. Thank you.
We're just happy to be of service—though\nI admit it warms my heart to hear you\npraise them.
More than even being praised myself...
Huh? Are you giving me a present?
Saint Starfall only gives presents to\ngood children.
Yeah, he—wait, how do you not know\nthat?
Er, I was simply testing your knowledge!\n*whinny*
So, you think you've been bad, then?
So bad you don't deserve presents?
Yeah... I had a big fight with my dad.
I said some really nasty stuff I didn't even\nmean, and...
Are you even listening? I don't deserve\nany presents!
＂Based on what we just heard,\nyou very much do.＂\n...says Saint Starfall.
You said some unpleasant things to your\nfather, which you know was bad.
But you see, the fact that you're aware of\nthat means you're a good person at heart.
So you should feel no shame accepting\nthese presents.
O-okay, but why are you giving me two?
One is for you, and the other is for your\nfather. You should give it to him and\nmake things right.
Okay! I'll give him this and apologize,\nright now!
I guess there really ARE good dragons!
That boy didn't say anything unpleasant\nto you, did he?
Oh, thank goodness our little Saint\nStarfalls are safe!
We talked for a while, but he was nothing\nbut kind. Why?
You see, the boy's father doesn't think\nvery highly of dragons.
I heard he's been raising his son to feel\nthe same, which is simply awful.
His father goes beyond ＂disliking＂ dragons,\nI'm afraid. I've heard some terrible things\nleave his lips in town.
He seems to think they ＂all need to be\nwiped out.＂ Can you believe that?!
Oh, it gets worse. Apparently they both\nbelong to the dragon-killing Syrol tribe.
Are you all right, lad?\nYou've gone deathly pale.
(I know that name all too well...)
(Those monsters murdered my tribe—\nalong with Felyx and Fydon's parents.)
